OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FThailand jails lawyer who  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fcalled for royal reform    
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, One of Thailand's most prominent       
OL,6, political activists, Arnon Nampa, has  
OL,7, been sentenced to four years in prison 
OL,8, under the country's much-criticised    
OL,9, royal defamation, or lese-majeste law. 
OL,11,FHe was convicted by a court in Bangkok 
OL,12,Fover comments he made during a protest 
OL,13,Fin October 2020.                       
OL,15,FThailand's lese-majeste law forbids    
OL,16,Fanyone from insulting the monarchy on  
OL,17,Fpain of harsh jail sentences.          
OL,19,FIt has been increasingly enforced since
OL,20,Fthe military took power in a 2014 coup.
